<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[155,794,164,1956]" lastBlockId="15.[840,1479,164,1956]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[179,259,1290,1312]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.— A member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[480,629,1290,1312]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Brookesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[480,629,1290,1312]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brookesia minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group based on small body size (
<collectionCode box="[346,390,1319,1341]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SVL</collectionCode>
&lt;
<quantity box="[410,480,1319,1341]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
) and molecular phylogenetic relationships. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frank Glaw &amp; Jörn Köhler &amp; Ted M. Townsend &amp; Miguel Vences" authorityYear="2012" box="[300,442,1346,1368]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Brookesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="micra">
<emphasis box="[300,442,1346,1368]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brookesia micra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all other members of the group by a shorter relative tail length (tail length/ 
<collectionCode box="[225,272,1403,1425]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">SVL</collectionCode>
0.37–0.49 versus 0.49–0.92), and by orange coloured tails in life in adults (vs. inconspicuous brownish colour). In addition, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frank Glaw &amp; Jörn Köhler &amp; Ted M. Townsend &amp; Miguel Vences" authorityYear="2012" box="[300,400,1458,1480]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Brookesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="confidens">
<emphasis box="[300,400,1458,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. confidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
